messageBody:
Over the thousands of years of it's existence the Latin alphabet
has aquired several parralel systems of communication closely
assocciated to it. Some of the letters in sign language are exact
copies of their written forms. Braille is designed for the current 26
letter alphabet and maritime flags are the same.
Perhaps one of the underlying reasons several reform systems
(including the Read alphabet for now) have not been accepted. Also,
with a new order for the alphabet, and different names for the
letters, what should the musical notes, when reffered to as C, D, E,
F, ect... be called?
